This paper discusses the integration of Prolog with an external object-oriented system, which is a topic that falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the design of the integration mechanism, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of XPCE, which is a graphical user interface toolkit, indicating a possible connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the integration mechanism to other external OO systems, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) if these systems are used for data analysis and prediction.
